Panic and anxiety have gripped residents of Hilton in KwaZulu-Natal after the first case of Covid-19 was confirmed in their town. DURBAN - Panic and anxiety has gripped residents of Hilton in KwaZulu-Natal after the first case of COVID-19 was confirmed in the town. Cowan House Preparatory School closed after reports that the patient’s children were pupils there. The Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize accompanied by the KZN MEC’s for Health Nomagugu Simelane-Zulu and Education Kwazi Mshengu have met with parents and management. READ: Mkhize speaks aKZN man 'feeling much better' after coronavirus diagnosis Travellers have been thrown into panic mode in the wake of the first coronavirus case in the country and has resulted in a number of flights being cancelled. KwaZulu -Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala has urged people not to panic and says one recorded case recorded does not mean an outbreak is imminent. 